History searches do not support the 'issuetype' field.
{noformat}
Please add this capability.

In the Document [Restoring a Project from backup|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver071/restoring-a-project-from-backup-802592982.html] below is mentioned.
{code:java}
Note, the Project Import tool will lock out your instance of JIRA during the actual data import (not during the validations), so please ensure that your instance does not need to be accessible during this time. {code}

I have tested the same using JIRA version 7.7 and I was able to access JIRA. Either please remove this point from the documentation OR if JIRA applies a lock in the backend some where then it will be helpful if there is a better explanation.

h3. Problem Definition
Currently when Jira Datacenter has lost global task (see related JRASERVER-47045, JRASERVER-66204), there is no way to remove this task. All nodes still thinks task is running, so this prevents corresponding operations to be done. 

h3. Suggested Solution
Create a plugin and/or health-check which lists running cluster tasks, show possible stuck and allow to remove them. 
 
h3. Workaround 
Workaround via ScriptRunner in Script Console, From [JRASERVER-66204?focusedCommentId=2280767|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-66204?focusedCommentId=2280767&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-2280767]

# List all live tasks:
{code:Java|borderStyle=solid}
import com.atlassian.jira.component.ComponentAccessor
import com.atlassian.jira.task.TaskManagerImpl
 
def TaskManager = ComponentAccessor.getComponent(TaskManagerImpl)
def tasks = TaskManager.getLiveTasks()
 
for(key in tasks){
    log.info 'Taskid: ' + key.getTaskId() + ' Description: ' + key.getDescription() + ' Start Time:' + key.getStartedTimestamp() + ' Username: ' + key.getUserName()
}
{code}
# Find stuck job and copy <Taskid> number
# Kill such Taskid, replacing xxxxxxx with Taskid number
{code:Java|borderStyle=solid}
import com.atlassian.jira.component.ComponentAccessor
import com.atlassian.jira.task.TaskManagerImpl
 
def TaskManager = ComponentAccessor.getComponent(TaskManagerImpl)
TaskManager.removeTask(xxxxxxx)
{code}

